We will begin the lesson part now.
As you know, our topic is to analyse strong players games,
and to try to understand how they think and why they played certain moves.
Together with that, we usually get some ideas about the opening theory as well as repeating some tactics.
The game we will study today is from European Championship 2002.
It is so unfair we studied so many male games until now, so to be fair, we have a female player in this game.
The black player is women World Champion, Yulia Savrasova.
who is she, and is she beautiful:)
she is very strong player, of course.
the player with white color is Russian Champion Aleksander Klimashin.
Klimashin chose the strongest 5th move, and let Yulia attack there.
is there any chance to know about the 5th alternate??
Yulia offered the alternative 5th move to i9.
And Klimashin was certain that Savrasova does not know the win there,
so he decided to let her play the main 5th move.
As you see, even in WC final the 5th move occurred so many times.
Even I lost there as black . :)
